OL,3,CPost Office Inquiry: Ed Davey 'sorry'
OL,4,Cfor taking five months to meet Alan
OL,5,CBates
OL,7,FReflecting on the response, he said:
OL,8,F"I am sorry that it took me five
OL,9,Fmonths to meet Sir Alan Bates, the man
OL,10,Fwho has done so much to uncover all
OL,11,Fthis, and that I did not see through
OL,12,Fthe Post Office's lies when I and my
OL,13,Fofficials raised his concerns with
OL,14,Fthem."
OL,16,FThe Post Office scandal is recognised
OL,17,Fas the most extensive miscarriage of
OL,18,Fjustice in UK history.
