OL,3,CPost Office Inquiry: Ed Davey 'sorry'
OL,4,Cfor taking five months to meet Alan
OL,5,CBates
OL,7,FAt Thursday's inquiry, he said: "I am
OL,8,Fdeeply sorry for the individuals and
OL,9,Ffamilies who have had their lives
OL,10,Fruined by it."
OL,12,FDavey said he relied on advice from
OL,13,Fcivil servants, and was unsure whether
OL,14,Fhe was misled by them - or if they too
OL,15,Fwere misled by the Post Office.
OL,17,F"If I had known then what we all know
OL,18,Fnow ` if the Post Office had told the
OL,19,Ftruth ` of course I would have acted
OL,20,Fdifferently," he said.
