OL,3,CPost Office Inquiry: Ed Davey 'sorry'
OL,4,Cfor taking five months to meet Alan
OL,5,CBates
OL,7,FSimilarly, Rebecca Thompson from
OL,8,FComputer Weekly, who wrote to McFadden
OL,9,Fhighlighting flaws in IT and deficits
OL,10,Fin accounts, was dismissed.
OL,12,FMcFadden had regrets over not "doing
OL,13,Fmore to question these (Post Office)
OL,14,Fresponses".
OL,16,FWhen asked why he did not look into
OL,17,Fthese cases, with many journalists and
OL,18,FMPs highlighting their concerns, the
OL,19,FLabour MP said: "I believe if I had
OL,20,F(questioned it more) I would have got
OL,21,Fthe same response from the Post Office.
