OL,3,CPost Office Inquiry: Ed Davey 'sorry'
OL,4,Cfor taking five months to meet Alan
OL,5,CBates
OL,7,F"I'm struck by how empathic their
OL,8,Fdefence of the system was, and
OL,9,Fcontinued to be, for a long time. Not
OL,10,Fonly an emphatic defence, but also the
OL,11,Fuse of court judgements as a
OL,12,Fproofpoint.
OL,14,F"When you have the use of court
OL,15,Fjudgements as a proofpoint, ministers
OL,16,Fat that point will usually think 'I
OL,17,Fcan't intervene in court judgments',
OL,18,Fand they think that for a good reason."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
